CSS Transitions
  - allows us to control the timing of visual state changes
  
  transition-property: color
    - the property we want to transition
 
 transition-duration: 1s
    - duration of transition
 
 transition-delay: 250ms
    - specifies the time to wait before startingthe transition
  
  transition-timing-function: 
    - describes the pace of the transition
      - ease in
        - starts slow, accelerates quickly, stops abruptly
      - ease out
        - begins abruptly, slows down, and ends slowly
      - ease-in-out
        - starts slow, gets fast in the middle, and ends slowly
      - linear
        - constant speed throughout
 
 transition: color 1.5s linear 0.5s
  - transition-property
  - duration
  - timing-function
  - delay
  and
 transition: color 1.5s linear 0.5s,
 font-size 750ms ease-in  100ms;
 and 
 transition: all 1.5s linear 0.5s;
